<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 2, 2025</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy describes how personal data is handled in the Hairelya app. By using the app, you agree to the practices described below.</p>

  <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
  <p>Hairelya does not collect or transmit any personally identifiable information. All data is stored securely on your device or, if enabled, in your private iCloud account.</p>

  <h2>2. Data Stored</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Treatment logs (name, date, frequency, products used)</li>
    <li>Hair timeline photos and notes</li>
    <li>Products used in your routine</li>
    <li>Routine preferences and reminder settings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. iCloud Sync</h2>
  <p>If you are a PRO user, your data is automatically synced with your personal iCloud account. Apple’s iCloud security and encryption protocols apply. We cannot access your iCloud data.</p>

  <h2>4. Notifications</h2>
  <p>The app uses local notifications to remind you about scheduled treatments or goals. No notification data is shared externally.</p>

  <h2>5. Ads</h2>
  <p>Hairelya FREE version may display banner ads. These are provided by third-party ad networks (such as Google AdMob) and may use anonymous identifiers for basic ad serving.</p>

  <h2>6. In-App Purchases</h2>
  <p>You can purchase a PRO subscription through Apple’s secure in-app purchase system (StoreKit). We do not store any payment information.</p>

  <h2>7. Data Deletion</h2>
  <p>You can delete all your data from within the app by removing it manually. Uninstalling the app will also remove local data. iCloud data must be deleted via iCloud settings.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. You will be notified of any major changes within the app.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:hairelya.app@gmail.com">hairelya.app@gmail.com</a></p>

</body>
</html>

